dfl2560PipeUsers.name: dfl2560PipeUsers
dfl2560PipeUsers.description: The current number of users, as defined by the grouping settings of each pipe, being tracked in the pipes system. Note that this value corresponds to the number of users active in each time slice of 1/20th of a second, and not to the number of users having open connections.

dfl2560PipeDefPrec.description: The precedence assigned to a packet for which has not one allready done by a Pipe Rule.

dfl2560PipeNumUsers.name: dfl2560PipeNumUsers
dfl2560PipeNumUsers.description: The current number of users, as defined by the grouping settings of each pipe, being tracked in the pipes system. This value corresponds to the number of users active in each time slice and not to the number of users having open connections.

dfl2560PipeCurrentBps.name: dfl2560PipeCurrentBps
dfl2560PipeCurrentBps.description: The current throughput of a pipe, in bits per second, as a sum of the corresponding values for all precedences.

dfl2560PipeCurrentPps.name: dfl2560PipeCurrentPps
dfl2560PipeCurrentPps.description: The current throughput of a pipe, in packets per second, as a sum of the corresponding values for all precedences.

dfl2560PipeDelayedPackets.name: dfl2560PipeDelayedPackets
dfl2560PipeDelayedPackets.description: The number of times packets have been delayed as a result of a pipe, or pipe user having used up its allotted bandwidth. Note that one single packet may be delayed several times; if a pipe is really full, this count may exceed the number of packets actually passing through the pipe.

dfl2560PipeDropedPackets.name: dfl2560PipeDropedPackets
dfl2560PipeDropedPackets.description: The number of packets dropped by a pipe. Packets are dropped when CorePlus is running out of packet buffers. This occurs when excessive amounts of packets need to be queued for later delivery. The packet dropped is always the one that has been queued the longest time globally, which means that the connection suffering from packet loss will be the one most overloading the system.

dfl2560PipePrecTable.name: dfl2560PipePrecTable
dfl2560PipePrecTable.description: There is a one to many relation between a pipe and its precedences. The number of precedences is a instance attribute of each pipe. This table extends the pipes table in order to express the relation between a pipe and the respective precedences.

dfl2560PipePrecEntry.name: dfl2560PipePrecEntry
dfl2560PipePrecEntry.description: An entry of the table of pipe pecedences. These table entries are chracterized by been indexed by two values. The first index the same as the pipe index of the corresponding row in table of pipes and the second index is the index of the set of precedences of the corresponding pipe.

dfl2560PipePrecIndex.name: dfl2560PipePrecIndex
dfl2560PipePrecIndex.description: Index of a precedence of a specific pipe. This is the second index of the entries of pipe precedence table described by object dfl2560PipePrecEntry.

dfl2560PipePrecBps.name: dfl2560PipePrecBps
dfl2560PipePrecBps.description: The current throughput of the pipe, in bits per second, with the corresponding precedence.

dfl2560PipePrecTotalPps.name: dfl2560PipePrecTotalPps
dfl2560PipePrecTotalPps.description: The current throughput of the pipe precedence, in packets per second.

dfl2560PipePrecReservedBps.name: dfl2560PipePrecReservedBps
dfl2560PipePrecReservedBps.description: The current bandwidth allocated to the precedence.

dfl2560PipePrecDynLimBps.name: dfl2560PipePrecDynLimBps
dfl2560PipePrecDynLimBps.description: The current bandwidth limit limit applied the precedence.

dfl2560PipePrecDynUsrLimBps.name: dfl2560PipePrecDynUsrLimBps
dfl2560PipePrecDynUsrLimBps.description: The current precedence bandwidth limit per user of the pipe.

dfl2560PipePrecDelayedPackets.name: dfl2560PipePrecDelayedPackets
dfl2560PipePrecDelayedPackets.description: The number of times packets have been delayed as a result of a precedence, or pipe user having used up its allotted bandwidth. Note that one single packet may be delayed several times; if a pipe is really full, this count may exceed the number of packets of this precedence actually passing through the pipe.

dfl2560PipePrecDropedPackets.name: dfl2560PipePrecDropedPackets
dfl2560PipePrecDropedPackets.description: The number of pipe dropped packets with the corresponding precedence.
